# Markdown to HTML Converter Demo

This is a **demonstration** of the Markdown to HTML converter tool. It showcases various *Markdown features* that are supported.

## Headers

### This is an H3 header
#### This is an H4 header
##### This is an H5 header
###### This is an H6 header

## Text Formatting

**Bold text** and __also bold__ text examples.

*Italic text* and _also italic_ text examples.

You can also combine ***bold and italic*** formatting.

## Lists

### Unordered List
- First item
- Second item
- Third item
  - Nested item (manual indentation)
  - Another nested item

### Ordered List
1. First numbered item
2. Second numbered item
3. Third numbered item

## Links and Code

Here's a link to [Google](https://www.google.com) and an auto-link: https://github.com

Inline code example: `console.log("Hello, World!");`

### Code Block

```javascript
function greet(name) {
    return `Hello, ${name}!`;
}

const message = greet("World");
console.log(message);
```

```python
def fibonacci(n):
    if n <= 1:
        return n
    return fibonacci(n-1) + fibonacci(n-2)

print(fibonacci(10))
```

## Blockquotes

> This is a blockquote. It can contain multiple lines
> and will be formatted appropriately in the HTML output.

> Another blockquote example.

## Horizontal Rules

Here's a horizontal rule:

